# 🧠 ANTIGRAVITY BUILD PROTOCOL

For: AI Freight Outbound SaaS
Stack: Next.js + Clerk + Convex + Stripe + Resend + WhatsApp + OpenAI

## 1️⃣ CORE PRINCIPLE

Build the smallest production-ready system that:
- Sends automated outbound
- Tracks replies
- Automates follow-ups
- Has unified inbox
- Is secure
- Is scalable

No feature creep.
No marketing pages.
No unnecessary abstractions.

## 2️⃣ DEVELOPMENT PHASE ORDER (MANDATORY)

Antigravity must follow this exact order:

### Phase 1 – Data & Auth
- Convex schema
- Clerk integration
- Organization model
- Role-based access
- NO UI beyond basic layout until schema is stable.

### Phase 2 – Messaging Core
- Lead model (limit to ~300 companies per country initially)
- Campaign model
- Message queue system
- WhatsApp provider wrapper
- Email provider wrapper
- Webhook handlers
- Status tracking
- Only after messaging works end-to-end move forward.

### Phase 3 – AI Layer
- Message generation wrapper
- Reply classification
- AI reply suggestion
- Caching layer for generations
- AI must be isolated in `/providers/openai.ts`.

### Phase 4 – Automation Engine
- Follow-up logic
- Behavior rules
- Rate limiting
- Retry logic

### Phase 5 – Billing
- Stripe Checkout
- Webhook
- Entitlement enforcement
- Usage tracking

## 3️⃣ ARCHITECTURE RULES

Antigravity must follow:

### A. Convex Is Source of Truth
UI never assumes state.
Everything reads from Convex.

### B. All Providers Wrapped
Create:
`convex/providers/`
- `whatsapp.ts` (Meta WhatsApp Cloud API)
- `email.ts` (Resend)
- `openai.ts`
- `stripe.ts`

No provider logic inside UI or random files.

### C. Idempotency Required
Every outbound message must include:
- `idempotencyKey`
- `providerMessageId`
- `status lifecycle`

No duplicate sends allowed.

### D. Webhooks Must Be:
- Signature verified
- Idempotent
- Safe against replay
- Logged minimally

## 4️⃣ DATA MODEL RULES

### Lead Storage & Scale
- **Master List**: Master leads (300 per country across 10 countries, total ~3,000) are stored externally.
- **Activation**: Leads are inserted into Convex ONLY when a campaign targeting them is started.
- **Cleanup**: Inactive leads with no replies are archived to maintain system performance.

Mandatory tables:
- `organizations`
- `users`
- `leads`
- `campaigns`
- `messages`
- `replies`
- `messageQueue`
- `events`
- `entitlements`

Every table must:
- Have indexes
- Validate input with zod
- Enforce org ownership

## 5️⃣ MESSAGE QUEUE PROTOCOL

Never send messages directly from UI.

Flow:
1. Campaign creates messages
2. Messages inserted into `messageQueue`
3. Background worker processes queue
4. Provider sends
5. Status updated
6. Event written

Retry logic:
- 3 attempts max
- Exponential backoff
- Permanent failures marked

## 6️⃣ AI COST CONTROL PROTOCOL

Antigravity must:
- Generate messages once per lead per campaign
- Cache results
- Enforce character limits
- Never re-generate unnecessarily
- Log token usage

## 7️⃣ SECURITY PROTOCOL

Required:
- Clerk auth validation on every mutation
- Org-based access control
- Webhook signature verification
- No raw PII logging
- No secrets in Convex

## 8️⃣ UX RULE

System must work with:
Minimum required inputs:
- Company name
- Sender identity
- Connected WhatsApp
- Connected email

Everything else defaulted.
No configuration overload.

## 9️⃣ CODE QUALITY RULES

Antigravity must:
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Avoid `any`
- Use `async/await` only
- No unused exports
- No commented dead code
- No UI fetching providers directly
- Server-side only for sending

## 🔟 FAILURE HANDLING RULES

All failures must:
- Be caught
- Be logged
- Update message status
- Not crash worker

## 11️⃣ TEST MODE REQUIRED

Add: `TEST_MODE=true`

When enabled:
- No real messages sent
- Provider calls mocked
- Webhooks simulated
- This prevents accidental spam during dev.

## 12️⃣ WHAT ANTIGRAVITY MUST NOT DO

- Do not add Redis
- Do not add Prisma
- Do not add unnecessary background systems
- Do not introduce microservices
- Do not redesign architecture mid-build
- Do not over-engineer abstractions

Keep stack minimal.

## 🧩 OPTIONAL BUT SMART

After core is stable:
- Add feature flags
- Add admin debug panel
- Add message health score
- Add basic analytics dashboard
- Only after stable messaging.

## 🚀 FIRST TIME USER FLOW (DAY 1)

Follow this exact flow for the onboarding experience:

1. **Step 1: Sign Up**
   - Login with Clerk.
   - Create company profile (name, website, main trade lane).
   - Connect WhatsApp number (Meta API) and Email (Resend).

2. **Step 2: Choose Target**
   - User selects: Target (Importer/Exporter/etc), Lane (Origin/Destination), and Industry.
   - User clicks **Start Campaign**.
   - *Constraint*: No message editing or template configuration at this stage.

3. **Step 3: System Takes Over**
   - Leads are selected automatically.
   - AI generates personalized messages.
   - Messages are queued and sends start daily.

## 📥 DAILY USE SCENARIO

- **Dashboard**: Shows send/delivery/reply/interest stats.
- **Inbox**: Unified view with AI-detected intent and suggested replies. One-click send.
- **Pipeline**: Drag-and-drop leads through stages (Lead -> Replied -> Qualified -> Quoting -> Won).

## 🏁 DEFINITION OF DONE (FINISHED STATE)

The system is considered "finished" when:
- [ ] Create org + connect channels (WhatsApp + email) ✅
- [ ] Import/add leads ✅
- [ ] Create campaign → generates messages → queues sends ✅
- [ ] Worker sends + updates statuses via webhook ✅
- [ ] Replies appear in unified inbox ✅
- [ ] AI suggests reply + intent label ✅
- [ ] Follow-up automation runs ✅
- [ ] Stripe plan gates sending limits ✅
- [ ] TEST_MODE works end-to-end (no real sends) ✅

## 🛠️ PR & COMMIT RULES

- **One feature per PR**: Keep changes focused and atomic.
- **CHANGELOG required**: Every PR must include a short entry in `CHANGELOG.md`.
- **Mandatory Tests**: Include at least 1 test for any webhook, queue, or rate-limit changes.
- **Dependency Control**: No new dependencies unless explicitly justified in the PR description.

## 🛑 STOP CONDITIONS (ASK USER)

Antigravity must stop and ask for clarification before:
- Any schema change that deletes or renames fields.
- Choosing between provider platforms (e.g., Twilio vs Meta) if not explicitly decided.
- Any pricing or billing logic assumptions.
- Any UI redesign beyond basic functional layouts.

## 🔥 FINAL INSTRUCTION TO ANTIGRAVITY

Build production-safe outbound infrastructure.

Stability > fancy UI
Correct state > speed
Security > features
Automation > customization
